<h1>Problem 1154 - 2022 DAMO, P5 of 6, G</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 8</h2>
<p>In triangle \(ABC\), \(D\) is an arbitrary point on \(BC\). \((ADC), (ADB)\) cut \(AB\), \(AC\) at \(F\) and \(E\) respectively. Tangents to \((ABC)\) at \(B\) and \(C\) intersect at \(X\). \(Z=EF \cap BX\) and \(Y=EF \cap CX\). \(P\) is a point on \((ABC)\) such that \(AP, YZ, BC\) are concurrent. Prove that \(P\) lies on \((XYZ)\).</p>
